<i> to share with you.</i>

573
00:27:05,290 --> 00:27:07,090
I wanna hear
all four points.

574
00:27:07,092 --> 00:27:08,291
It's called...
I am ready.

575
00:27:08,293 --> 00:27:09,425
It takes a village...

576
00:27:09,427 --> 00:27:11,060
Best opening
to a title ever.

577
00:27:11,062 --> 00:27:12,629
Not a Batman.

578
00:27:13,430 --> 00:27:14,464
Waiter.
Sir?

579
00:27:14,466 --> 00:27:15,598
Can I?
Of course.

580
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:16,966
Thank you.
My pleasure.

581
00:27:16,968 --> 00:27:18,034
Thanks so much.

582
00:27:20,270 --> 00:27:22,105
What?
<i> Look.</i>

583
00:27:22,107 --> 00:27:26,109
<i> Batman's been on the job</i>
<i> for a very, very, very,</i>

584
00:27:26,111 --> 00:27:28,478
<i> very, very, very, very,</i>

585
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,646
<i> very long time.</i>

586
00:27:29,648 --> 00:27:31,581
He has aged phenomenally.

587
00:27:31,583 --> 00:27:35,652
<i> However, despite all the great</i>
<i> work Batman has done for us,</i>

588
00:27:35,654 --> 00:27:37,620
<i> Gotham city</i>
<i> is still the most</i>

589
00:27:37,622 --> 00:27:40,590
<i> crime-ridden city</i>
<i> in the world.</i>

590
00:27:40,592 --> 00:27:41,991
She's got
a great point.
Interesting.

591
00:27:41,993 --> 00:27:43,926
Historically speaking,
that is accurate.

592
00:27:43,928 --> 00:27:45,495
<i> He hasn't captured riddler.</i>
You know,
she's right.

593
00:27:45,497 --> 00:27:46,996
<i> He hasn't captured bane.</i>

594
00:27:46,998 --> 00:27:49,098
Huh!
<i> Or catwoman.</i>

595
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:53,136
<i> Or two-face, or any</i>
<i> of Gotham's other villains!</i>

596
00:27:53,138 --> 00:27:54,337
He's not good
at his job.

597
00:27:54,339 --> 00:27:56,005
